        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:58PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over McRae. This storm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
McRae, Alamo, Mount Vernon, Helena, Glenwood, Milan, Ailey, Scotland,
Higgston, Little Ocmulgee State Park, and Workmore.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
